code: import pandas as pd import numpy as np import torch import torch.nn as nn import torch.optim as optim from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader from torchvision import transforms, models from torchvision.models import efficientnet_b4, EfficientNet_B4_Weights from PIL import Image import os from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split import faiss from tqdm import tqdm # Prepare data with hotel filtering original_df = pd.read_csv("input/train.csv") original_df["image_path"] = original_df.apply( lambda r: f"input/train_images/{r.chain}/{r.image}", axis=1 ) counts = original_df["hotel_id"].value_counts() valid_hotels = counts[counts >= 2].index df_filtered = original_df[original_df["hotel_id"].isin(valid_hotels)].copy() hotel_ids = df_filtered["hotel_id"].unique() hotel_id_to_idx = {hid: idx for idx, hid in enumerate(hotel_ids)} idx_to_hotel = {v: k for k, v in hotel_id_to_idx.items()} df_filtered["hotel_idx"] = df_filtered["hotel_id"].map(hotel_id_to_idx) train_df, val_df = train_test_split( df_filtered, test_size=0.2, stratify=df_filtered["hotel_idx"], random_state=42 ) # Enhanced transforms with augmentation train_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.RandomResizedCrop(224, scale=(0.6, 1.0)), transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(), transforms.ColorJitter(0.3, 0.3, 0.3, 0.1), transforms.RandomRotation(15), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) val_transform = transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(256), transforms.CenterCrop(224), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize(mean=[0.485, 0.456, 0.406], std=[0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) class HotelDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, transform=None): self.df = df self.transform = transform def __len__(self): return len(self.df) def __getitem__(self, idx): row = self.df.iloc[idx] img = Image.open(row["image_path"]).convert("RGB") if self.transform: img = self.transform(img) return img, row["hotel_idx"] train_loader = DataLoader( HotelDataset(train_df, train_transform), batch_size=32, shuffle=True, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True, ) val_loader = DataLoader( HotelDataset(val_df, val_transform), batch_size=64, shuffle=False, num_workers=8, pin_memory=True, ) model = efficientnet_b4(weights=EfficientNet_B4_Weights.IMAGENET1K_V1) model.classifier = nn.Linear(model.classifier[1].in_features, len(hotel_ids)) model = model.cuda() criterion = nn.CrossEntropyLoss(label_smoothing=0.1) optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=1e-4, weight_decay=1e-5) scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.ReduceLROnPlateau( optimizer, "max", patience=2, factor=0.5 ) best_map = 0 for epoch in range(5): # Increased epochs model.train() for imgs, labels in tqdm(train_loader, desc=f"Epoch {epoch+1}"): imgs, labels = imgs.cuda(), labels.cuda() optimizer.zero_grad() outputs = model(imgs) loss = criterion(outputs, labels) loss.backward() optimizer.step() model.eval() all_preds, all_true = [], [] with torch.no_grad(): for imgs, labels in val_loader: outputs = model(imgs.cuda()) probs = torch.softmax(outputs, 1) _, top5 = torch.topk(probs, 5, dim=1) all_preds.extend( [[idx_to_hotel[i.item()] for i in row] for row in top5.cpu()] ) all_true.extend(labels.tolist()) map_sum = 0 for true_idx, pred in zip(all_true, all_preds): true_hid = idx_to_hotel[true_idx] for k, p in enumerate(pred[:5], 1): if p == true_hid: map_sum += 1 / k break val_map = map_sum / len(all_true) print(f"Val MAP@5: {val_map:.4f}") if val_map > best_map: best_map = val_map torch.save(model.state_dict(), "best_model.pth") scheduler.step(val_map) print(f"Best Validation MAP@5: {best_map:.4f}") # Generate submission model.load_state_dict(torch.load("best_model.pth")) model.eval() embedding_model = nn.Sequential(model.features, model.avgpool, nn.Flatten()).cuda() class EmbeddingDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, df, transform=None): self.df = df self.transform = transform def __len__(self): return len(self.df) def __getitem__(self, idx): row = self.df.iloc[idx] img = Image.open(row["image_path"]).convert("RGB") if self.transform: img = self.transform(img) return img # Generate embeddings with validation transform train_embeddings = [] with torch.no_grad(): for imgs in tqdm( DataLoader( EmbeddingDataset(original_df, val_transform), batch_size=128, num_workers=8 ), desc="Embedding", ): train_embeddings.append(embedding_model(imgs.cuda()).cpu().numpy()) train_embeddings = np.concatenate(train_embeddings) hotel_ids_all = original_df["hotel_id"].values index = faiss.IndexFlatIP(train_embeddings.shape[1]) faiss.normalize_L2(train_embeddings) index.add(train_embeddings) class TestDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, img_dir, transform=None): self.img_paths = [ os.path.join(img_dir, f) for f in os.listdir(img_dir) if f.endswith(".jpg") ] self.transform = transform def __len__(self): return len(self.img_paths) def __getitem__(self, idx): img = Image.open(self.img_paths[idx]).convert("RGB") if self.transform: img = self.transform(img) return img, os.path.basename(self.img_paths[idx]) test_dataset = TestDataset("input/test_images", val_transform) test_loader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=128, num_workers=8) test_embeddings, test_names = [], [] with torch.no_grad(): for imgs, names in tqdm(test_loader, desc="Testing"): test_embeddings.append(embedding_model(imgs.cuda()).cpu().numpy()) test_names.extend(names) test_embeddings = np.concatenate(test_embeddings) faiss.normalize_L2(test_embeddings) D, I = index.search(test_embeddings, 100) submission = [] for name, neighbors in zip(test_names, I): seen = set() preds = [] for idx in neighbors: hid = hotel_ids_all[idx] if hid not in seen: preds.append(str(hid)) seen.add(hid) if len(preds) == 5: break submission.append([name, " ".join(preds)]) os.makedirs("submission", exist_ok=True) pd.DataFrame(submission, columns=["image", "hotel_id"]).to_csv( "submission/submission.csv", index=False ) print(f"Submission saved with {len(submission)} predictions") print(f"Final Validation MAP@5: {best_map:.4f}")
